  "body": "My apologies for probably not posting in the right place (I did poke around a bit but didn’t see the obvious place for this type of post). Any guidance will be appreciated.\r\n\r\nI’m working on a smart contract for my project’s ICO to support start/cliff/duration-style vesting tokens, written as an ERC20 trait contract. Tokens can be granted by a grantor role, but can only be spent by the holder once vested. This capability may be useful for projects having investors or employees compensated in tokens.\r\n\r\nI’m new to solidity and while learning I stumbled upon openzeppelin-solidity, and very much like what I’ve seen here. So I decided to adopt this group’s practices because they’re aligned with mine.\r\n\r\nI’ve developed my ERC20-style contract so that it can be applied to another contracts, implementing specifically the needed capabilities around granting and vesting of tokens.\r\n\r\nI have been working to this group’s standards to the best of my understanding, in hopes I might be able to contribute my work here, as others may find it useful.\r\n\r\nWhat is the next step? Do I create an ERP or it’s equivalent requesting the capability, then open a discussion about it? I’ve completed the work needed for my project including thorough unit testing, and for my project, my work is done. But I realize additional work will likely be needed here, and my work may not be submittable in its current form without working with this group to generate consensus around how it should look.\r\n\r\nYour guidance and feedback are welcome. Please suggest how best I should proceed. Thanks!",
